description: TEHRAN - Korea used a big second half to beat Iran, 83-60, and reach the FIBA U18 Asia Cup 2024 Quarter-Finals, Wednesday at the Prince Hamza Hall.
title: Repeat-seeking Korea zoom past Iran, barge into Quarter-Finals

description: PARIS – Iranian archer Mohmmadreza Arab Ameri seized a bronze medal in the 2024 Paralympic Games on Wednesday.
title: Iran Arab Ameri wins bronze in archery: 2024 Paralympics

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Ambassador to the United Nations in New York, Amir Saied Iravani, has said that the Israeli regime is threatening countries in the West Asia region with "nuclear annihilation", warning the regime’s nuclear arsenal poses a significant threat to both regional and global peace and security.
title: ‘Israel’s nuclear arsenal poses major threat to global peace’

description: TEHRAN - Representatives from over 20 Muslim countries convened in Damghan, Iran, to mark the life and legacy of the late Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian.
title: Muslims honor Amir Abdollahian, reiterate support for Palestinians in Damghan conference

description: Egypt's President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi arrived in Ankara on Wednesday in his first official visit to Turkey since becoming president 10 years ago.
title: Egypt's Sisi visits Turkey for first time after 12-year rift with Erdogan

title: Gaza truce: Netanyahu caught between the devil and the deep blue sea

title: Para shooter Javanmardi announces retirement

description: TEHRAN - The International Day of Charity is held annually on September 5 with the objective of sensitizing and mobilizing people, NGOs, and stakeholders all around the world to help others through volunteer and philanthropic activities.
title: International Day of Charity: global solidarity to eradicate poverty

description: PARIS – Iranian javelin thrower Saeid Afrooz claimed a gold medal at the 2024 Paralympic Games on Wednesday.
title: Javelin thrower Afrooz wins gold medal at 2024 Paralympics

description: TEHRAN – Over the past two months, a total of 1,515 prisoners of unintentional crimes were released.
title: More than 1,500 prisoners of unintentional crimes freed

description: TEHRAN - Iran has strongly advised the Western countries against continuing to back Tel Aviv’s crimes against Palestinians, saying it is like betting on the “losing horse” because the “terrorist gang” ruling Israel is facing “strategic impasse” to ensure the regime’s “survival”.
title: Tel Aviv rulers facing strategic impasse to ensure Israel’s survival: Iran

description: TEHRAN - Today marks the 30th day of the lunar month of Safar, commemorated as the martyrdom anniversary of Imam Reza (AS), the eighth Shia Imam. In observance of this solemn occasion, a significant number of pilgrims have embarked on a spiritual journey on foot to his holy shrine in Mashhad.
title: Over 400,000 pilgrims expected to walk to Imam Reza shrine for martyrdom anniversary

description: TEHRAN – There are more than 511,000 housewives in the country under insurance coverage, an official with the Social Security Organization has said.
title: Over half a million housewives under coverage of insurance

description: TEHRAN - The average age of women in Iran giving birth to their first child stood at 27.4 years in the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year that started on March 21, according to a report by the National Organization for Civil Registration.
title: Average age of first-time mothers in Iran is 27.4: report

description: TEHRAN- The value of non-oil export from Markazi province in the center of Iran increased by 56 percent during the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-August 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, a provincial official announced.
title: Non-oil export from Markazi province up 56% in 5 months yr/yr

description: TEHRAN- The value of Iran’s potato export reached $52 million during the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-August 21), the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) reported.
title: Iran exports $52m of potato in 5 months

description: TEHRAN- As announced by an official with Iran’s Agriculture Ministry, the country’s honey production per capita stands at 1.415 kilograms.
title: Honey production per capita stands at 1.415kg in Iran

description: TEHRAN – As announced by a provincial official, 4.871 million tons of oil products and non-oil goods were loaded and unloaded at the ports of the west of Hormozgan province, in the south of Iran, during the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20- August 21).
title: Loading, unloading of goods exceeds 4.8m tons at ports of west Hormozgan

description: TEHRAN- The value of Iran’s export of petrochemical products increased by 12.8 percent during the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-August 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, the head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) announced.
title: Iran’s petchem export increases 12.8% in 5 months on year
